vectorData.altText: 12. The aponeuroses of which muscles contribute to the formation of the conjoint tendon?
That's right!  The internal oblique and the transversus abdominis fuse to form conjoint tendon, when inserts into pubic crest.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

Superior to the pubis, the aponeuroses of the internal oblique and the transversus abdominis fuse to form the conjoint tendon, which inserts into the pubic crest. This structure contributes to the inguinal canal (see 3.1 part 2).
